>
  <p>In cardiology, fatigue often reflects a mismatch between the body's oxygen needs and supply. Heart failure reduces cardiac output, leading to poor perfusion of organs such as muscles and the brain. This results in a lack of energy and cognitive slowing.</p>

  <p>Rhythm disorders impair ventricular function and reduce haemodynamic efficiency, causing fluctuating fatigue, sometimes associated with dizziness. Myocardial ischaemia limits the heart's energy reserves, worsening the sensation of exhaustion during exertion.</p>

  <p>When faced with unexplained and persistent fatigue, a cardiac evaluation is recommended.</p>
</DetailLayout>
